-- Aviva says to double excess cashflow by end of 2016
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 02:12AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, July 9 (Reuters) - UK insurer Aviva <AV.L> said on Wednesday that it planned to double annual excess cashflow to 800 million pounds ($1.36 billion) by the end of 2016 as it it laid out the next stage of its turnaround plan.

It would also look to reduce its operating expense ratio to below 50 percent over the same period, the company said in a statement.